data.title: Elizabeth I - Vocab, Definition, and Must Know Facts
data.meta_description: Elizabeth I was the Queen of England and Ireland from 1558 until her death in 1603. She is often referred to as the "Virgin Queen" because she never married or had children. Her reign, known as the Elizabethan era, was a time of significant cultural, economic, and political progress in England.
data.text:
Definition

Elizabeth I was the Queen of England and Ireland from 1558 until her death in 1603. She is often referred to as the "Virgin Queen" because she never married or had children. Her reign, known as the Elizabethan era, was a time of significant cultural, economic, and political progress in England.
